# 6. 奇妙な演出家

Emu: Wooow! All these tiny robots are scuttling around him!
???: Once upon a time there was an eccentric alchemist.
Tsukasa: And those look like...drones? That's a modern take on puppet theater...
Emu: Oooh! They're flying now!
???: Thanks to the wonders of alchemy, he lived a life free of worries, but that made the common townsfolk envious.
???: One day, a traveling theater group visited the town. The alchemist took a peek at the show and saw that it made the townsfolk very happy. It was then that he made a decision.
???: He decided that he too wanted to stage marvelous shows that everyone would enjoy!
Emu: Yeah! I'm like that too!
Tsukasa: (Using robots and drones in a show for kids is pretty out there, but what he's doing is certainly impressive.)
Tsukasa: (The narration is well-paced, and his gestures are expressive. He skillfully manages to make the audience sympathize with the robots, too!)
Tsukasa: (Could he have created this performance entirely by himself? If so, I want him as our stage director!)
???: The alchemist came up with his own ideas, and rehearsed them alone, trying to match the performance of the traveling theater troupe.
???: Eventually, he invited the townsfolk to see his show. And when they did—
Security Staff's Voice: YOU AGAIN!
Tsukasa: Hmm?
???: Oh dear. It seems we're due for an unscheduled intermission. We'll continue the story some other time!
Emu & Kids: Nooo!
???: Was the alchemist's show a success? For now, I shall leave that to your imagination!
Security Staff: Stop right there! *Huff*... He always gives me the slip!
Tsukasa: Excuse me, but was that guy not a park employee?
Security Staff: No. He comes here to stage unauthorized performances. He makes himself scarce whenever I warn him, but keeps coming back.
Emu: When can I hear the rest of the story? I want to know if the townsfolk liked the alchemist's show!
Tsukasa: Hey, did you already forget what we were doing? We were supposed to be looking for new members for our troupe.
Tsukasa: (He would've been a good pick, though.)
Tsukasa: Sigh... We searched the entire park for members who'd like to join us, but to no avail.
Classmate: What's up, Tsukasa? You got that job at Phoenix Wonderland, right? How was your first day?
Tsukasa: I encountered a monster who couldn't be reasoned with, got teleported to another world, and was threatened by a fiendish mascot!
Classmate: Um... Is that a play?
Tsukasa: If only that'd been just a play...
Tsukasa: By the way, have you ever seen a guy doing shows with robots anywhere around here?
Classmate: So you've finally lost it, huh?
Tsukasa: How rude! I'm perfectly sane!
Classmate: Come on, though, shows with robots? Hmm... Wait a minute...
Tsukasa: Oh? You know someone who fits the bill?
Classmate: There's this guy who transferred to the class next door recently. Rui Kamishiro.
Classmate: He must be smart, because he transferred from an elite high school, but he's a bit of a weirdo. He brings all these machines to school and does shows out in the street and stuff.
Tsukasa: Tell me everything you know!
Tsukasa: To think he was hiding right under my nose this whole time.
Tsukasa: Hi, I'm Tsukasa Tenma from Class A. I'm looking for Rui Kamishiro.
Student From Class B: Rui? He's gone off somewhere. I don't know where.
Tsukasa: So I just missed him... Can you at least tell me where he usually hangs out? Or could I leave a message for him?
Student From Class B: Sorry but I don't want to have anything to do with him. He whispers to himself and chuckles during classes like he's crazy.
Tsukasa: The more I learn about him, the more he seems like an oddball. Well, I'll have a look around the school, and maybe I'll find him.
Tsukasa: He wasn't in the courtyard, or the cafeteria. This is the last place I could think of.
Tsukasa: Sigh... But the only people who hang out on the rooftop at this hour are couples and weirdos...
Tsukasa: Hang on...
Rui: Hey there, Tsukasa. I've been waiting for you to show up. You wanted to talk to me about something?
Tsukasa: What? How did you know?
Rui: I've been watching you.
Tsukasa: What? Don't tell me you're...a fan?!
Rui: Fan? Hehe, it's interesting that that's the conclusion you jumped to.
Rui: You might say I'm a fan of yours. Look up, Tsukasa.
Tsukasa: Huh?! Is that a drone? Is that what you meant when you said you've been watching me?
Rui: Yes, indeed. It amused me to see you running all over school, looking for me. I couldn't resist having my drone follow you.
Tsukasa: It's got a camera and a mic?! Did you make this thing?
Rui: I did indeed.
Tsukasa: And the robots at the show you did yesterday? Did you make those too?
Rui: Oh, you saw my show? I wasn't aware that you were one of MY fans.
Tsukasa: I didn't come here as a fan. I'm here to offer you an invitation!
Rui: To what?
Tsukasa: I'll get to the point, I want you to make shows with me!
Rui: Is that right? Hmm, that's not an unappealing idea.
Tsukasa: I knew you'd agree! Okay, now that I have you on board—
Rui: It seems we share a penchant for theater. I wish you the best of luck, Tsukasa. Let's meet again some other time!
Tsukasa: Wait, what?
